  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Inbox-to-Knowledge Forwarding: Send & Copy Content to Pages\n\nAdd frictionless mechanisms within the Inbox that allow users to forward email content — either in full or selectively — directly to relevant pages , eliminating the need to manually copy-paste between contexts.\n\nRequirements:\n\nCore \"Send to Page\" Action\n- Add a \"Send to Page\" contextual action on each email item (accessible via hover action bar, right-click context menu, and keyboard shortcut)\n- Open a command-palette-style modal that lets the user search and select a destination page: an Page or new page.  http://localhost:3000/workspace\n- Support sending the full email (subject, body, sender, timestamp) as structured content to the target page\n- Append rather than overwrite when the target page already contains content \n\nSelective \"Copy to Page\" via Text Selection\n- When a user selects text within an email body, surface a floating mini-toolbar with a \"Copy to Page\" option\n- Allow the selected excerpt to be sent to a destination page with the source email referenced as a citation (sender, date, subject)\n- Support quick-send to a recently used or pinned destination without reopening the full search modal\n\nDestination Page Types & Behavior\n\n- Kanban Card: append content to the card's description or post it as a new comment in the activity feed; optionally pre-fill a new card title from the email subject\n\n- New Page (quick-create): allow users to create a new Kanban card or Open Brain entry inline from the modal without leaving the Inbox\n\nUX & Interaction Details\n- Show a non-intrusive confirmation toast after a successful send, with an inline link to the destination page\n- Preserve the original email's read/unread state after forwarding (do not auto-mark as read)\n- Support bulk selection of multiple emails with a single \"Send all to Page\" operation\n- Remember the last-used destination per session to reduce repetitive searching\n\nTechnical Considerations\n- Reuse the existing Kanban card comment and description update APIs; no new write endpoints required for card destinations\n- Sanitize HTML email bodies before storing to prevent XSS in downstream page renderers\n- Ensure forwarded content respects row-level user ownership — users can only send to pages they own\n\nEdge Cases\n- Email body is empty or contains only attachments: prompt user to add a note before sending, or send attachment metadata as a reference\n- Destination card or record has been deleted: surface a clear error and offer to create a new destination instead\n- Very long email threads: offer a \"Send summary only\" option that truncates to the first N characters or uses AI summarization before forwarding",
  "title": "Send emails to pages with selective copying",
